WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:04.069
An AI Agent does not forget only because information is missing.

2
00:00:03.536 --> 00:00:09.649
It can also lose focus because too much undifferentiated information competes for a finite attention budget.

3
00:00:09.121 --> 00:00:13.244
First, manage the whole context state, not only the prompt.

4
00:00:12.713 --> 00:00:19.172
Keep goals, constraints, tools, evidence, and current state according to what changes the next decision.

5
00:00:18.661 --> 00:00:21.053
Second, raise signal quality.

6
00:00:20.499 --> 00:00:28.227
Use instructions at the right altitude, a minimal tool set, and a few canonical examples instead of brittle rules and edge-case piles.

7
00:00:27.730 --> 00:00:30.391
Third, retrieve detail on demand.

8
00:00:29.861 --> 00:00:36.714
Keep stable essentials up front and let the Agent progressively open changing or specialized material through clear references.

9
00:00:36.240 --> 00:00:43.324
Finally, protect long tasks with compaction, structured notes, and the six-part Minimum High-Signal Context Pack.

10
00:00:42.793 --> 00:00:46.906
Keep the signal, retrieve the detail, and preserve the working state.

11
00:00:46.355 --> 00:00:48.189
Follow Tiny Agent.

12
00:00:47.666 --> 00:00:50.692
Tiny Agent helps you get better at using AI.
